               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; names of the protagonist and of the angel Gäbrǝʾel (fols. 89rb, 99va-100ra, 107rb, 107vb, 109rb); names of the donors; words addressing the reader on fols. 11rb, 22ra; elements of the punctuation signs and of the text dividers; elements of Ethiopic numerals.&#xD;
&#xD;
Several groups of lines on the incipit page of Text I (alternating with black lines); two or three initial lines in the incipit of sections (homilies), sometimes alternating with black lines (e.g., fols. 61rb, 89ra, 97vb); one or two initial lines of subsections (miracles and commemorative notices); the first word in the incipit of subsections (hymns), i.e. sälam "salutation".</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Text I-6 does not include an ʾarke-hymn.</note>
                  </msItem>
